      <button class="modal-close" id="modal-close">Start with free — I'll explore later</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Premium teasers — clear, not blocking -->
  <section class="premium-teasers">
    <div class="teaser-row">
      <a href="/upgrade" class="teaser-card">
        <span class="teaser-icon">📋</span>
        <div>
          <strong>15+ sources with one-liners</strong>
          <p>Every link I scanned this week, ranked.</p>
        </div>
        <span class="teaser-arrow">Pro →</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/upgrade?tier=inner" class="teaser-card teaser-gold">
        <span class="teaser-icon">🛠️</span>
        <div>
          <strong>CLAUDE.md, agent configs, scripts</strong>
          <p>The exact setup I use. Copy-paste ready.</p>
        </div>
        <span class="teaser-arrow">Inner Circle →</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Latest digest — full free content, no fade blocking -->
  {latest ? (
    <section class="latest-digest">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>This Week's Digest</h2>
        <p class="digest-date">{formatDate(latest.data.date)}</p>
      </div>

      <div class="digest-full">
        <latestContent.Content />
      </div>
    </section>
  ) : (
    <div class="no-content">
      <p>First issue coming soon. Subscribe above to be the first to know.</p>
    </div>
  )}

  <!-- Bottom fade teaser — soft preview of premium content -->
  <section class="bottom-teaser">
    <div class="bottom-teaser-content">
      <div class="blurred-sources">
        <p class="source-line">Claude Code just shipped auto mode. Here's what it means for your workflow...</p>
        <p class="source-line">OpenClaw 2026.3.23 update: DeepSeek plugin, Qwen pay-as-you-go, new pricing...</p>
        <p class="source-line">Polsia hit $1M ARR. The agent that builds startups. Real numbers inside...</p>
        <p class="source-line">LM Studio compromised? 1020 upvotes. Check your install immediately...</p>
        <p class="source-line">Jensen Huang: if your engineer isn't burning $250K in tokens, something's wrong...</p>
        <p class="source-line">Harvard professor co-authored a paper with Claude in 2 weeks. It would've taken...</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bottom-teaser-fade"></div>
      <div class="bottom-teaser-cta">
        <h3>15+ more sources this week</h3>
        <p>Pro members get the full source list, community access, and early delivery every Friday.</p>
        <a href="/upgrade" class="btn btn-primary">See what you're missing</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About -->
  <section class="about">
    <h2>Why this exists</h2>
    <div class="about-text">
      <p>I was spending 2 hours a day reading AI news and still missing things that mattered. So I built an AI agent that does it for me — scans 700+ sources, scores every article by builder relevance, filters out the noise, and gives me the 20 that actually matter.</p>
      <p>Now I'm sharing that feed with you. Every story earns its spot. No AI slop, no filler, no "delve into the landscape." Just the tools, launches, and shifts that affect what you're building this week.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="value-grid">
      <div class="value-card">
        <h3>Stanford-trained, builder-first</h3>
        <p>I'm an engineer who builds AI agents full-time. This newsletter is what I wish existed when I started.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="value-card">
        <h3>AI that curates AI news</h3>
        <p>The system that makes this newsletter is itself an AI agent. It learns what matters to builders and gets smarter every week.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="value-card">
        <h3>Tools you can use Monday morning</h3>
        <p>MCP servers, CLAUDE.md templates, agent configs, scripts. Not theory — things you copy-paste into your stack.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="value-card">
        <h3>Zero AI slop guarantee</h3>
        <p>25 banned phrases. Every summary sounds like a text from a smart friend, not a corporate memo written by ChatGPT.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="site-footer">
    <p>Built by a Stanford engineer, for builders. <a href="/archive">Archive</a> · <a href="/pro">Pro Library</a> · <a href="/upgrade">Upgrade</a></p>
  </footer>

  <style>
    .home-header {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 3rem 0 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 3.5em;
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
